  <main>
    <section class="intro">
      <h2>Why it matters to me</h2>
      <p>
        I was seven years old when I saw the ocean for the first time. My whole
        family spent a week in Puerto Vallarta, and the mix of warm sand,
        bright sunsets, and lively streets shaped my idea of a perfect
        vacation forever.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="highlights">
      <h2>Simple reasons to love Puerto Vallarta</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Friendly waterfront:</strong> The Malecón boardwalk is full of art, music, and local food.</li>
        <li><strong>Golden beaches:</strong> Soft sand and gentle waves make it easy to relax or learn to swim.</li>
        <li><strong>Sierra Madre views:</strong> A short bus ride takes you from the coast to lush green hills.</li>
        <li><strong>Fresh seafood:</strong> Shrimp tacos at sunset are a must-try.</li>
        <li><strong>Cultural mix:</strong> Modern resorts sit next to historic cobblestone streets and colorful markets.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="facts">
      <h2>Quick facts</h2>
      <div class="fact-grid">
        <div class="fact">
          <h3>Founded</h3>
          <p>1851 (as Las Peñas)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h3>Average sea temp</h3>
          <p>26 °C / 79 °F</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h3>Best months</h3>
          <p>November – April (dry season)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h3>Airport code</h3>
          <p>PVR</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

